As of the [[census]]<ref name="GR2">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|access-date=2008-01-31|title=U.S. Census website}}</ref> of 2000, there were 8,860 people, 3,533 households, and 2,158 families residing in the city. The population density was {{Pop density|3494.1|1|sqmi|km2}}. There were 3,851 housing units at an average density of {{Pop density|1518.7|1|sqmi|km2}}. The racial makeup of the city was 82.4% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 8.2% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0.59% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 0.64% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0.02% [[Pacific Islander (U.S. Census)|Pacific Islander]], 2.19% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 2.26% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 7.5% of the population.

There were 3,533 households, out of which 32.4% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 39.9% were married couples living together, 15.6% had a female householder with no husband present, and 38.9% were non-families. 32.6% of all households were made up of individuals, and 15.1% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.48 and the average family size was 3.15.

[[File:Deerpark Reformed Church Port Jervis.jpg|thumb|upright|The Deerpark Reformed Church on East Main Street was originally organized in 1737, making it the oldest congregation in the area.  The current building dates from 1838.<ref>City of Port Jervis historical marker at the church site</ref>]]

In the city, the age distribution of the population shows 27.8% under the age of 18, 8.4% from 18 to 24, 28.3% from 25 to 44, 20.3% from 45 to 64, and 15.2% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 36 years. For every 100 females, there were 91.4 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 86.0 males.

The median income for a household in the city was $30,241, and the median income for a family was $35,481. Males had a median income of $31,851 versus $22,274 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the city was $16,525. About 14.2% of families and 15.7% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 25.5% of those under age 18 and 10.3% of those age 65 or over.

